<Content>charming old world convinient for transport and reasona This hotel is a converted apartment budilding from 1910, one of a few pre WW2 buildings still intact in the area. There are still some apartments in the building so teh feel is very residential. The lift is from 1913 a real relic but still functioning and adds to teh overall charm of the place. The U-bahn is 200m from the hotels entrance and taxis from the centre of Berlin are apporx 12 euros at night. Breakfast was a good german style buffet and service was great. The rooms were very spacious with herringbone parquet and modern decor.All in all an excellent choice, convinient for transportation and very reasonably priced at approx 60 euros per night. 
